title: MDA-MB-231P exosomes
characteristics_ch1: parental non-brain metastatic cell line: MDA-MB-231P
growth_protocol_ch1: After 72 hours of cell culturing, 10 ml of culture media was centrifuged at 3000 x g for 15 min to remove cells and cell debris. The supernatant was mixed with 2 ml of ExoQuick-TC, refrigerated for 16 hours and then centrifuged at 1500 x g for 30 min at 4°C to obtain the exosomes pellet.
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA from exosomes was isolated using mirVana miRNA isolation kit (Life Technologies, Grand Island, NY)
label_protocol_ch1: 10 ng of total RNA were reverse transcribed with miScript II RT kit (Qiagen, Germantown, MD) according to manufacturers’ guidelines. 20 μl of cDNA was diluted with RNase-free water prior to the PCR reaction.  Real-time PCR for mature miRNA expression profiling was developed using the SYBR Green-based human breast cancer pathway-focused miScript miRNA PCR array (Qiagen, Germantown, MD) on a StepOnePlus 96-well RT PCR instrument (Applied Biosystems, Grand Island, NY).
data_processing: The normalization and all the data analysis were performed according to the manufacturers instructions using their web-based software package: http://pcrdataanalysis.sabiosciences.com/mirna/arrayanalysis.php. The relative quantity of the target miRNA was normalized using Syn-cel-miR-39 miScript miRNA Mimic miRNeasy Spike-In Control (Qiagen, Germantown, MD) that was exogenously added during RNA purification. The web-based software package automatically performs all deltadeltaCt based fold-change calculations from the uploaded raw threshold cycle data.
data_processing.1: Fold-Change file reports test/control (ie, brain metastatic cell-derived exosomes/non brain metastatic cell derived-exosomes).  Linked as supplementary file on Series record.
